<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52586986-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s454"><num value="454">§ 454.</num><heading> Practice of law by justices and judges</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any justice or judge appointed under the authority of the United States who engages in the practice of law is guilty of a high misdemeanor.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52586987-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/908">62 Stat. 908</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52586988-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52586989-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 373 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s258">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 258</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1161">36 Stat. 1161</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes in phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
</notes>
